==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peristyle
<hw>Per"i*style</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peristylum</ets>, Gr. <grk>peri`stylon</grk>,
<grk>peri`stylos</grk>; <grk>peri`</grk> about + <grk>sty^los</grk> a
column: cf. F. <ets>p⟦eacute⟧ristyle</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>A range of columns with their entablature, etc.; specifically, a
complete system of columns, whether on all sides of a court, or
surrounding a building, such as the cella of a temple. Used in the
former sense, it gives name to the larger and inner court of a Roman
dwelling, the <ex>peristyle</ex>. See <er>Colonnade</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perisystole</ent>⟦br⟧
